| image2 = Suwa Taisha Maemiya Honden.jpg | caption2 = 上社前宮（長野県{{ill|Chino|ja|茅野市|12=draft|12=draft}}）
| image3= 諏訪大社 春宮 神楽殿.JPG | caption3= 下社春宮（長野県{{ill|Shimosuwa|ja|下諏訪町|12=draft|12=draft}}）
| image4 = Suwa taisha Shimosha Akimiya , 諏訪大社 下社 秋宮 - panoramio (7).jpg | caption4 = 下社秋宮（長野県下諏訪町） | footer_align = center | footer= 諏訪大社を構成する2社4宮}}
'''Suwa Shrine''' (諏訪神社) refers to shrines with "Suwa" in their name, particularly associated with {{ill|Suwa Faith|ja|諏訪信仰|12=draft|12=draft}}, a form of {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|12=draft|12=draft}} worship centered on {{ill|Suwa Grand Shrine|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview ==
There are approximately 25,000 Suwa Shrines throughout Japan, all having {{ill|Suwa Grand Shrine|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha|12=draft|12=draft}} in Nagano Prefecture as their head shrine. Suwa Faith revolves around the veneration of {{ill|Takeminakata no Kami|ja|建御名方神|12=draft|12=draft}}, the main deity, and his consort {{ill|Yasakatome no Kami|ja|八坂刀売神|12=draft|12=draft}}. Together, they are referred to as the "Suwa Deities" (諏訪大神). When Suwa Grand Shrine's deities are transferred to other Suwa Shrines, their divine spirits are believed to reside within a ritual {{ill|Nagi Kama|ja|薙鎌|12=draft|12=draft}}, which becomes the sacred object of the shrine.
Suwa Grand Shrine conducts the renowned {{ill|Onbashira Festival|ja|御柱祭|12=draft|12=draft}}, held every six years. Many Suwa Shrines across the country host similar festivals. Additionally, rituals like the spring {{ill|Ontōsai|ja|御頭祭|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Misayama Festival|ja|御射山祭|12=draft|12=draft}}, a traditional hunting ceremony in late August, are celebrated at various Suwa Shrines.
== List of Main Suwa Shrines == === Head Shrine === * {{ill|Suwa Grand Shrine|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in Suwa, Chino, and Shimosuwa in Nagano Prefecture.
=== Hokkaido === * {{ill|Suwa Shrine (Sapporo)|ja|諏訪神社 (札幌市)|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Sapporo|ja|札幌市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Higashi-ku|ja|東区|12=draft|12=draft}}) * {{ill|Hanaiso Suwa Shrine|ja|花磯諏訪神社|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Nishi District|ja|爾志郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Otobe|ja|乙部町|12=draft|12=draft}})
=== Tohoku Region === [[File:Akita-Suwa-gū.jpg|thumb|Akita Suwa Shrine]] ; Aomori Prefecture * {{ill|Suwa Shrine (Aomori)|ja|諏訪神社 (青森市)|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Aomori|ja|青森市|12=draft|12=draft}}) * {{ill|Suwa Shrine (Nanbu)|ja|諏訪神社 (青森県南部町)|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Nanbu|ja|南部町|12=draft|12=draft}})
; Akita Prefecture * '''{{ill|Akita Suwa Shrine|ja|秋田諏訪宮|12=draft|12=draft}}''' ({{ill|Misato|ja|美郷町|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Listed as a special shrine (別表神社).
=== Kanto Region === ; Tokyo [[File:Suwa Shrine 20190515(3).jpg|thumb|Suwa Shrine (Tachikawa, Shibasaki)]] * {{ill|Suwa Shrine (Tachikawa)|ja|諏訪神社 (立川市柴崎町)|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Tachikawa|ja|立川市|12=draft|12=draft}})
=== Chubu Region === ; Nagano Prefecture [[File:霧降宮切久保諏訪神社 Kirihuminoya Kirikubo Suwa shrine.jpg|thumb|Kirifuri-no-Miya Kiri-kubo Suwa Shrine]] * {{ill|Kamisuwa Shrine|ja|上諏訪神社|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Ōmachi|ja|大町市|12=draft|12=draft}}) * {{ill|Shimosuwa Shrine|ja|下諏訪神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Nagano Prefecture, Omachi City)
=== Kyushu Region === [[File:Nagasaki-Suwa-Shrine-1558.jpg|thumb|Chinzei Taisha Suwa Shrine]] ; Nagasaki Prefecture * '''{{ill|Chinzei Taisha Suwa Shrine|ja|鎮西大社諏訪神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''' ({{ill|Nagasaki|ja|長崎市|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Listed as a special shrine.
== References == {{Reflist}} == See Also == {{Commonscat|Suwa-jinja}} * {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|タケミナカタ|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Mishaguji|ja|ミシャグジ|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Chikuma Shrine|ja|生島足島神社|12=draft|12=draft}}
